title: 'Hawks sixth at Beloit Memorial Invite
text:
'Hawks sixth at Beloit Memorial Invite 
BELOIT — The Fort Atkinson girls’ swim team had some individual winners in its sixth-place-out of-seven finish at the Beloit Memorial Invitational on Saturday. 
The Blackhawks gathered 209 points, edging out Delavan Darien while Lake Geneva Badger won the event with 793 points. 
“Saturday's meet was a great one,” said Fort head coach Evan Hill. “Not only did the girls perform well winning several events but we had multiple season personal bests. Leading the way once again was Mariah Marowsky as she won the 200-yard free style and 100 free style setting meet records in the process for both races.” 
Marowsky continued her strong freshman season with a 55.95 in the 100 and 2:01.79 in the 200. 
Though the freshman was the only individual winner on the day, Fort still got some points out of its relay teams and senior Bailey Weston. 
Weston earned third place for both the 100 and 200 free style with personal best times in both races. The senior swam a 57.42 in the 100 and a 2:03.90 in the 200. 
Devon Oliver and Molly Bare joined Marowsky and Weston for the 200 free relay, taking a third place finish with a time of 1:51.32. 
Bare, Weston and Marowsky also took a second place finish in the 150 free relay, which took place instead of the 400-yard, clocking in at 1:21.29. 
The Blackhawks will return home on Tuesday, hosting McFarland at 6 p.m.
